  <tr>
   <td class="spacer"></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
  <td width="580" colspan="2" valign="top">
  <!-- Start Update Input -->
  <center>Well hot damn, a tad over a month since our first kill and we 
finally had the force online AND on the back lawn of Xegony's summer 
getaway.  I've been trying without any success to get another X win under 
our belts.  I've never seen so many ppl ninja or flatout not bother to 
log in when X was announced as a potential target.  Our first fight was 
so close and so long, nearly 47 minutes, that we were pretty put off by 
having to get back up there and not be able to produce another win.  
Well, it is with great pride that I can say we straight up worked the 
Lawn Fairy over tonight.  First pull, Xegony = Deaderson.   Grats to 
Krokpot on those silly mnk/bst claws, Aerial on the Wand and myself on 
the chain legs.<br><br>

But, it gets better, before we put down Xegony, we swung by Fire and 
visited Fennin for another melee yawnfest fight.  He's not much in terms 
of challenge and I really am puzzled why that particular fight has to go 
down the way it does.  I'm not gonna complain tho, he's just part of the 
Elemental Gravy Train known to FE...  In a bit less then 3 months, we 
have managed to procure nearly 700 Elemental Plane Loot Drops with our 
sole access to the elemental planes.
<br><br>

Last week, we managed to get everyone and their sister keyed for PoEB.  
Which by the way, was a fantastic idea in terms of flagging for a zone. 
I'm not sure why they can't adapt that idea to the rest of the zones. 
Where you could recieve up to 72 Keys per kill and the ability to hand 
them out as ppl required... hellfire, that would allow for guilds to not 
constantly farm lame lame content over and over again.  <br><br>

I'm not gonna post any screenshots because everything has been posted 
everywhere else and it's much quicker for me to just type this up.  FE 
been so damn close on Coirnav 3 times now that I can taste the win.  Then 
it'll be firing up the tractors and switching to massive god farm mode 
until SoE decides we've paid them enough money to play their game while 
we wait for content; read Rathe encounter and PoTime. Content mind you, 
that we paid for 6 months ago when we purchased the game!!</center>
  <!-- End Update Input -->
  </td>
 </tr>
